HEADWORD: Knabble
<hw>Knab"ble</hw> <pr>(n⟦acr⟧b"b'l)</pr>, <pos>v. i.</pos> <ety>[Freq.
of <ets>knab</ets>.]</ety> <def>To bite or nibble.</def>
<mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>Horses will <qex>knabble</qex> at walls, and rats gnaw iron.</q>
<rj><qau>Sir T. Browne.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Knack</ent>⟦br⟧
